{
  "text": "As approximately 50% of cancer patients receive RT with the primary goal of local tumor control (4), combinatory therapies of RT with immune checkpoint inhibitors targeting T cells might be a good synergistic option to induce additional systemic antitumor immune responses, as it has already been shown in many mouse models (Table 2 ) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . A tremelimumab/SBRT pilot study for patients suffering from unresectable pancreatic cancer (NCT02311361) is currently recruiting patients.",
